track_notes: This is a challenging hike.  It is on trail the whole way, but the 4,400+ feet of climbing will thrash your quads.  Starts nice and easy along Miller Creek, at about 1.5mi you enter Saguaro National Park and it starts getting rocky.  about 4 miles up you reach Happy Valley Campground which is a beautiful flat area in tall pines - it would be a fantastic spot to camp for a multi-day activation excursion.  The final half mile to the summit is steep and brutal.  Views from the top are spectacular.  I made the mistake of doing this hike on a day when temperatures in Tucson were 105+ degrees, and I drank over 2 gallons of liquid and still felt dehydrated (and that is a lot of pack weight).  But the length of the hike means that activating in cooler winter months may be challenging due to the shorter days.
track_title: Rincon Peak via Miller Creek Trail
